<item>
            <title>[SPARK-23785] LauncherBackend doesn&apos;t check state of connection before setting state</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23785</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Found in&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-18533&quot; title=&quot;Add option to use InProcessLauncher to submit spark jobs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-18533&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-18533&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; while trying to integration with the &lt;tt&gt;InProcessLauncher&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;tt&gt;LauncherBackend&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t check the state of its connection to the &lt;tt&gt;LauncherServer&lt;/tt&gt; before trying to run &lt;tt&gt;setState&lt;/tt&gt; - which sends a &lt;tt&gt;SetState&lt;/tt&gt; message on the connection.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13147580">SPARK-23785</key>
            <summary>LauncherBackend doesn&apos;t check state of connection before setting state</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
